{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"patternMatch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"stringReversed","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Passing the correct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", this is more efficient if the reversed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_pattern_match()"},{"text":" will only construct it if the compiled pattern","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires reverse matches.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_pattern_match()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be obtained by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. This works only if the string","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pattern_match is deprecated:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use [method@GLib.PatternSpec.match] instead"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecRef\/PatternSpecProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib19PatternSpecProtocolPAAE12patternMatch12stringLength0G00G8ReversedSbSi_SPys4Int8VGSgAKtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14PatternSpecRefV","platforms":[],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"patternMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"extern